# ACCEPTED behavior (documented caveat): an f-literal DIRECTLY in a body interp
# `{ f`...` }` is a MARKUP TEMPLATE — static text is written raw (`.S`), holes are
# escaped. Contrast goexpr-f-literal/f_value_is_escaped_string, where the SAME
# f-literal used as a Go VALUE is a plain string (escaped whole). f-literal meaning
# is context-sensitive: markup template in body position, string in value position.
-- input.gsx --
package views
component Host(x string) {
	<div>{ f`<b>@{x}</b>` }</div>
}
-- invoke --
Host("hi")
-- diagnostics.golden --
-- render.golden --
<div><b>hi</b></div>
